\p
\v 21 Later \w I|strong="G2532"\w* \w went|strong="G2064"\w* \w north|strong="G2532"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* countries \w called|strong="G3588"\w* \w Syria|strong="G4947"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w Cilicia|strong="G2791"\w*.  
\v 22 \w But|strong="G1161"\w* back \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w Judea|strong="G2449"\w* country \w the|strong="G1722"\w* Christians \w there|strong="G1161"\w* didn’\w t|strong="G3588"\w* \w know|strong="G1722"\w* me.  
\v 23 \w They|strong="G1161"\w* \w only|strong="G3440"\w* heard \w people|strong="G1510"\w* \w say|strong="G1473"\w*, “\w The|strong="G1161"\w* \w man|strong="G3739"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* tried \w to|strong="G1161"\w* stop \w us|strong="G2097"\w* \w believing|strong="G4102"\w* \w in|strong="G4102"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G1510"\w* Christ, \w the|strong="G1161"\w* \w man|strong="G3739"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w gave|strong="G3588"\w* \w us|strong="G2097"\w* bad trouble \w and|strong="G1161"\w* hurt \w us|strong="G2097"\w*, \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w man|strong="G3739"\w* \w has|strong="G3739"\w* changed, \w and|strong="G1161"\w* \w now|strong="G1161"\w* \w he|strong="G1161"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* telling \w everyone|strong="G3739"\w* \w to|strong="G1161"\w* \w believe|strong="G4102"\w* \w in|strong="G4102"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G1510"\w* Christ.”  
\v 24 \w Those|strong="G3588"\w* Christians heard \w that|strong="G3588"\w* \w I|strong="G1473"\w* changed, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w were|strong="G3588"\w* happy, \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* thanked \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w said|strong="G2532"\w* \w that|strong="G3588"\w* \w he|strong="G2532"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* really \w great|strong="G2532"\w*.   
\c 2  
\s1 The church leaders in Jerusalem agreed with Paul  
\p
\v 1-2 Then, 14 years later, God told me to go to Jerusalem again. This time I went with Barnabas, and I took Titus with me too. We had a little meeting there, with just the important church people, and I told them all about the message that I teach to the people that are not Jews. I wanted to see if they agreed with what I was doing. I didn’t want anyone to mess up my work.\x * \xo 2:1-2 \xt Acts 11:30; 15:2\x*   
\p
\v 3-4 You see, Titus was there with me, and he is a Greek man, not a Jew. But there were some Jewish men that came secretly into the church in Jerusalem. They reckoned they believed in Jesus, but they didn’t really trust him properly. They only came into the church to see what we were doing. And they reckoned that Titus had to follow the Jewish law and have a young man operation. But, you see, if we belong to Jesus Christ, we are free from that law. But those men wanted to force us to keep that law.  
\v 5 \w But|strong="G3588"\w* \w we|strong="G3739"\w* didn’\w t|strong="G3588"\w* listen \w to|strong="G4314"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w*, \w not|strong="G3761"\w* \w even|strong="G3761"\w* \w a|strong="G3739"\w* little bit. \w We|strong="G3739"\w* knew \w they|strong="G3588"\w* \w were|strong="G3588"\w* wrong. \w So|strong="G2443"\w* \w we|strong="G3739"\w* didn’\w t|strong="G3588"\w* tell Titus \w to|strong="G4314"\w* \w have|strong="G5210"\w* \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w young|strong="G3739"\w* \w man|strong="G3739"\w* operation. \w You|strong="G5210"\w* see, \w we|strong="G3739"\w* only want \w to|strong="G4314"\w* teach \w the|strong="G4314"\w* \w true|strong="G3588"\w* message \w about|strong="G4314"\w* Jesus, \w and|strong="G3588"\w* \w we|strong="G3739"\w* want \w you|strong="G5210"\w* mob \w to|strong="G4314"\w* keep \w on|strong="G2443"\w* believing \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w true|strong="G3588"\w* message.   
\p
