\s1 Jesus lives in his people  
\p
\v 19-20 You see, I used to try to follow that law, so that law controlled me. I tried to do everything in that law, but I couldn’t do it, so the law said that I had to die. But then I stopped thinking about that law, and I turned around to follow Jesus, and now he controls me, and God makes me properly alive. And you know that Jesus died on a cross. Well, I believe in Jesus, so it is like I died there too. But Jesus is alive now, so I’m alive now too. You see, Jesus lives inside me, right here in my body. And he gets me to do the things that God wants me to do. He is God’s son. He loved me, and he gave up his life and died for me.  
\v 21 \w Yes|strong="G1063"\w*, \w God|strong="G2316"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* really \w good|strong="G1223"\w* \w to|strong="G3756"\w* us, \w and|strong="G2316"\w* \w he|strong="G3588"\w* really \w did|strong="G2316"\w* \w a|strong="G1487"\w* lot \w for|strong="G1063"\w* us. \w I|strong="G1063"\w* \w will|strong="G2316"\w* \w never|strong="G3756"\w* change \w my|strong="G1223"\w* mind \w about|strong="G3588"\w* \w that|strong="G3588"\w*. \w You|strong="G1487"\w* see, \w we|strong="G1063"\w* \w can|strong="G1063"\w*’\w t|strong="G3588"\w* become \w good|strong="G1223"\w* \w people|strong="G3588"\w* \w by|strong="G1223"\w* following \w the|strong="G1223"\w* \w law|strong="G3551"\w*. \w If|strong="G1487"\w* \w we|strong="G1063"\w* \w could|strong="G3588"\w* \w do|strong="G1223"\w* \w that|strong="G3588"\w*, \w it|strong="G1063"\w* \w would|strong="G2316"\w* mean \w that|strong="G3588"\w* \w Jesus|strong="G3756"\w* \w died|strong="G3588"\w* \w for|strong="G1063"\w* \w nothing|strong="G3756"\w*. \w But|strong="G1487"\w*, \w of|strong="G1223"\w* course, \w he|strong="G3588"\w* didn’\w t|strong="G3588"\w*.   
\c 3  
